{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/anotonio.silva/antonio/mms-last-attempt","sessionId":"adb72d37-dfad-4621-b289-1547f6c9a61d","version":"2.0.76","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a5e8e84","slug":"swirling-purring-ripple","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"# TASK: Find visual mockups, designs, and UI specifications\n\n## CONTEXT\nFor a frontend team to build something, they need to SEE what it should look like.\nMMS uses \"Semantic Zoom\" - heatmap, DNA blocks, task cards at different zoom levels.\n\n## SEARCHES\n1. Find image files:\n   find ~/antonio/mms -type f \\( -name \"*.png\" -o -name \"*.jpg\" -o -name \"*.jpeg\" -o -name \"*.svg\" -o -name \"*.gif\" \\) 2>/dev/null | head -100\n\n2. Find design documents:\n   find ~/antonio/mms -type f -name \"*design*\" -o -name \"*mockup*\" -o -name \"*wireframe*\" -o -name \"*ui*\" -o -name \"*screen*\" 2>/dev/null\n\n3. Look for Figma links or design references in markdown files:\n   grep -r \"figma\\|screenshot\\|mockup\\|wireframe\\|design\" ~/antonio/mms --include=\"*.md\" -l\n\n4. Check for any POC HTML files that show what was built:\n   find ~/antonio/mms -name \"*.html\" 2>/dev/null | head -50\n\n## OUTPUT\nReturn:\n- List of all visual assets found (with paths)\n- Any design documents\n- Screenshots of POCs that worked\n- References to external designs (Figma, etc)"},"uuid":"07c465aa-a9a0-4ba0-9cfe-69a3e05e380d","timestamp":"2026-01-06T18:31:54.035Z"}
